<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>We publish information on our energy consumption and report on our initiatives to reduce emissions and waste.</p>

<h2 id="greening-government-targets">Greening government targets</h2>

<p>The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/greening-government-commitments-targets">Greening government commitments</a> set targets for central government departments to reduce their environmental impact by 2015. We have exceeded all these targets. This includes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>reducing our greenhouse gas emissions by nearly half (43%)</li>
  <li>cutting the amount of waste we produce by 62%</li>
  <li>using a third less water</li>
</ul>

<p>This also means we’re making financial savings. We’ll keep improving our performance and aim to be even more efficient during 2015 to 2016.</p>

<p>The table below shows our performance for the 2014 to 2015 financial year, against a baseline for the 2009 to 2010 year. It compares our results to the cross-government performance.</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>2014 to 2015 GGC target versus 2009 to 2010 baseline</th>
      <th>DfE progress</th>
      <th>Cross-government progress</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Reduce greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions by 25%</td>
      <td>-43%</td>
      <td>-20%</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Cut domestic business travel flights by 20%</td>
      <td>-20%</td>
      <td>-18%</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Reduce the amount of waste we generate by 25%</td>
      <td>-62%</td>
      <td>22%</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Cut paper use by 10% in 2011-12</td>
      <td>-26%</td>
      <td>-30%</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Office estate water - m3/full time equivalent employee</td>
      <td>7.7</td>
      <td>7.5</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Reduce total estate water consumption (m3)</td>
      <td>-34%</td>
      <td>-9%</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Sustainable procurement and improve supply chain engagement</td>
      <td>Qualitative</td>
      <td>Not calculated</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

